Today's airstrikes targeted rebel-controlled army camps in the Red Sea port city of Hodeida, and hit warehouses belonging to a factory that produces dairy products .
At least 35 workers have been killed, many of them crushed by the rubble or burned to death .
Saudi Arabia hinted that it was prepared to launch a ground invasion in Yemen in the hope of forcing Houthi rebels to allow Houthi forces to return to the country .